TWO people received medical treatment after smoke from a fire in a wheelie bin spread to a block of flats. 2 injured by wheelie bin fire smoke TWO people received medical treatment after smoke from a fire in a wheelie bin spread to a block of flats.Crews were called to a three-storey building in Byres Road, Kilwinning, North Ayrshire, on Wednesday afternoon.Firefighters led a man and a woman safely from the flats within the block. They had suffered minor smoke inhalation. 